For the full cross-platform developer setup (dependencies, mise tasks, bootstrap
scripts, troubleshooting) see doc/BUILD.md. Quick paths: `./bootstrap.sh`
(macOS/Linux) or `./bootstrap-windows.sh` (MSYS2), or `mise run setup && mise run build`.

Build targets (all build ccutter + ct2util; the C64 player.bin is assembled by acme):

make                      -- Linux binary (ldc2)
make -f Makefile.mac      -- macOS binary / .app (ldc2; LIBSPATH=/opt/homebrew/lib)
make -f Makefile.win      -- Windows x64 binary (mingw-w64 + ldc2); see the file header
make-wintest.sh           -- package a Windows x64 zip with the required DLLs

Windows x64 (Makefile.win): the canonical build is a NATIVE build in an
MSYS2/mingw-w64 shell, run by the "windows" job in .github/workflows/build.yml
(it uses the MSYS2 `mingw-w64-x86_64-ldc` package, which is built for the mingw
GNU ABI). Cross-building from macOS/Linux is not possible with stock LDC: LDC's
druntime supports only the MSVC C runtime on Windows, so a windows-gnu (mingw)
runtime build fails (core/stdc/stdio.d "Unsupported platform"). Use the CI job
or an MSYS2 shell.
